Replace Google 3D Tiles with NASA Dingo Gap Mars tileset, add trimesh collision and vehicle LOD camera

- Swap Google Photorealistic Tiles for public NASA Dingo Gap Mars dataset (no API key needed)
- Rename GoogleTiles to Tiles3D, add Z-up to Y-up coordinate rotation
- Replace flat-box raycast collision with per-mesh Rapier trimesh colliders that track LOD swaps
- Add bounding box wall colliders to prevent driving off the tile edge
- Add vehicle LOD camera (PerspectiveCamera at car position) registered with tile renderer
  to force consistent high-res LOD near the car independent of chase camera orbit
- Fix frame ordering: vehicle camera updates at useFrame priority -1 (before tiles.update)
- Fix resolution registration: setResolutionFromRenderer must be called each frame or SSE ignores the camera
- Reduce near clipping plane to 0.001 with logarithmic depth buffer to prevent frustum clipping at low orbit
- Add wireframe debug viz for tile collision geometry and bounding box
- Update CLAUDE.md with full 3D Tiles architecture, LOD camera system, and edge artifact documentation
- Replace Vite boilerplate README with project summary, tech stack, and integrations

